        "hero.desc": "Resulting from long research, the products of the <strong>Ngon by SEM Production</strong> brand come from the industrial shelling and processing of hard-shelled tropical pumpkin seeds, 'African pistachios' specific to certain terroirs of Cameroon. Commonly called <em>pistachios</em>, their scientific name is <strong>Cucumeropsis mannii</strong>. They are produced by organic farming (+) with harvesting every two years.<br>It is the queen of cucurbits; it has many exceptional virtues in health, cosmetics, and dietetics.",

